The paper deals with improving the interaction between humans and AI systems, specifically in the context of handwritten digit classification. This falls under the broad category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between reducing misinterpretation by the AI system and improving efficiency of input generation for the human, which involves aspects of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of a deep learning system for classification suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The focus on handwritten digit classification and the use of a conditional convolutional autoencoder (CCAE) suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL).
